results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #293
results.description: Spider-Man lies buried while Kraven dons a Spider-Man costume to prove that he is the better of his foe in every way.  Plus, what horrible crimes is the Vermin about to commit?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #294
results.description: It's the startling conclusion to Kraven's Last Hunt.  After Kraven proves his superiority over Spider-Man, what is left for the hunter?  You must read this shocking ending.

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #298
results.description: Put together an arms shipment, terrorists, and the high-rolling mercenary called Chance, and what have you got? You've got pretty big trouble for everyone's favorite wall-crawler in "Chance Encounter”!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #318
results.description: The Scorpion's back- and he's got a new, deadlier tail! Scorpion's been hired to kidnap someone, but Scorpion turns the job into a plot to kidnap J. Jonah Jameson. Trouble is, the Jameson he tries to catch is really the Chameleon!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #353
results.description: The stalker cyborg Midnight is back on the scene, and it’s up to Spider-Man and Darkhawk to thwart his path of destruction! What is the Secret Empire unleashing these strange modes of technological warfare? And will Spidey be able to stop them at the source before more civilians suffer?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #354
results.description: The Secret Empire’s true agenda is revealed, leaving both Marvel heroes and villains up for grabs. Which hero has the Empire set their sights on? And will the combined might of Spider-Man, Nova, and Darkhawk be enough to stop the production of more cyborgs?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #355
results.description: Guest-starring Punisher and Moon Knight! Heroes of New York City unite to take down a common enemy in the Secret Empire. With Midnight under close watch, will pertinent answers about the Empire come to light?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #356
results.description: Inner machinations within the Secret Empire leave the whole operation vulnerable. Punisher remains shaken by the heroes’ battle with Midnight. With the Empire’s highest members struggling for power, will Spider-Man and company exploit a fatal flaw?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #360
results.description: Cardiac may not be as misinformed as Spider-Man believed, after a sinister plot by the TechToy Factory comes to light. A new victim of Carnage emerges. Peter must make a choice between saving one person’s life over another.

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #400
results.description: The status quo of Peter Parker’s life is shaken to the core in this Anniversary Special. Featuring a tale penned by Stan “The Man” Lee! Plus, the origin of Ben Reilly!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #401
results.description: Why is Peter Parker on the lam? And how will Spider-Man recover given last issue’s devastation?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #402
results.description: Spider-Man tries to clear the name of Peter Parker, but will Detective Raven be convinced? Meanwhile, there’s trouble on the home front with MJ, her unborn child, and Aunt May!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #403
results.description: Spidey is on trial for the murder of Louise Kennedy! With Carnage acting as the prosecutor, will our hero survive long enough to hear the sentence?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #404
results.description: It’s a full on Spider-Battle! Peter and Ben vs. Kaine, Spidercide and the Jackal! Which side will triumph in this Spider-Man Civil War?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #405
results.description: Ben’s Vermont getaway is cut short when Seward Trainer contacts him with an urgent call! Meanwhile, Peter Parker is tormented by a vivid nightmare he has no recollection of!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #406
results.description: While Peter and MJ get to the bottom of his nightmares, Doc Ock discovers that Seward has created a bridge between a virtual reality and the real world! Can Ben stop the 8-armed woman before it’s too late?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #407
results.description: From Scarlet Spider…to SPIDER-MAN! Ben Reilly dons the mantle of the original wall-crawler, but soon finds it’s true that with great power does come great responsibility!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #408
results.description: Better change the channel – Mysterio has taken over the airwaves, and with his new TV network MysteryVision, he turns anyone who watches into his mindless henchmen!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #409
results.description: THE RETURN OF KAINE continues! Kaine has eluded the Great Game for now, but the Rhino won't stop until Kaine joins up - whether he likes it or not! He'll have to team up with Spidey to get out of this one in one piece!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #410
results.description: THE BIRTH OF SPIDER-CARNAGE! While Cletus rots in jail, the sick symbiote is carving up The Big Apple! The only way for Spidey to stop it is to combine with it and become— the amazing Spider-Carnage! Continued in SPIDER-MAN #67!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #415
results.description: Onslaught uses a fleet of Sentinels to seize the city. After a Sentinel attack on the Daily Bugle, J. Jonah Jameson is actually happy see Spider-Man save the day. A Spider-Man/Onslaught crossover issue!

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #430
results.description: Carnage is on the rampage, and only Spider-Man stands in his way! Luckily, Peter Parker doesn't stand alone, thanks to the arrival of the Silver Surfer! But what secret history does the Surfer have with the symbiote?

results.title: Amazing Spider-Man (1963) #431
results.description: Carnage has abandoned Cletus Kasady…and bonded with the Silver Surfer! What chance does Spidey have against the seemingly unstoppable Carnage Cosmic?
